  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The spinal cord is a very important part of the central nervous system. fMRI can be applied
      to observe functional status of the human spinal cord. Under different conditions, the
      investigators will see different types of fMRI signals within the spinal cord. In resting
      state, the investigators might see active/inactive signals, too.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
